1
00:00:02.798 --> 00:00:04.158  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
( door opens )

2
00:00:05.517 --> 00:00:07.157  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
( door closes )

3
00:00:09.836 --> 00:00:11.395  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I didn't expect to find you here.

4
00:00:12.361 --> 00:00:13.595  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I thought you'd be down on the Promenade

5
00:00:13.675 --> 00:00:17.744  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
helping Mardah put up the decorations
for the Bajoran Gratitude Festival.

6
00:00:17.713 --> 00:00:19.473  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
That was the plan

7
00:00:19.993 --> 00:00:22.712  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
but it turns out I don't have
much to be grateful for.

8
00:00:23.552 --> 00:00:27.311  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
-Isn't that the earring you--
-Bought for Mardah, yeah. You want it?

9
00:00:27.111 --> 00:00:29.910  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Maybe you can give it to Major Kira
for her next birthday or something.

10
00:00:30.589 --> 00:00:32.829  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
( sighs ) All right.

11
00:00:32.909 --> 00:00:34.389  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Tell me about it.

12
00:00:36.588 --> 00:00:38.682  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Mardah's gone, Dad.

13
00:00:38.628 --> 00:00:41.546  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
She got accepted to the Science Academy
on Regulus III.

14
00:00:41.826 --> 00:00:42.986  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
That's a good school.

15
00:00:43.662 --> 00:00:45.186  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
It's 300 light-years away.

16
00:00:45.265 --> 00:00:47.145  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Jake, you're 16.

17
00:00:47.225 --> 00:00:49.424  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Take my word for it, you'll survive.

18
00:00:50.144 --> 00:00:52.103  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Sooner or later, you'll find someone else.

19
00:00:52.543 --> 00:00:53.383  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Who knows?

20
00:00:53.463 --> 00:00:56.222  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Maybe you'll find someone tonight
at the Gratitude Festival.

21
00:00:56.702 --> 00:00:57.902  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Yeah, sure.

22
00:00:57.982 --> 00:00:59.622  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Jake, the whole point of the festival

23
00:00:59.701 --> 00:01:02.820  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
is to put all your troubles behind you
and make a new start.

24
00:01:03.260 --> 00:01:04.700  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I could use one.

25
00:01:05.819 --> 00:01:08.819  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
-OK, I'll go.
-Good. That's the spirit.

26
00:01:09.658 --> 00:01:11.337  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
But I'm not going to have any fun.

27
00:01:12.297 --> 00:01:13.417  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Oh.

28
00:01:16.376 --> 00:01:17.895  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
( laughs ) Nervous, Chief?

29
00:01:18.656 --> 00:01:20.175  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
( laughs )

30
00:01:20.614 --> 00:01:21.495  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
What are you talking about?

31
00:01:21.574 --> 00:01:23.773  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
That's your fifth cup of coffee
in 20 minutes.

32
00:01:24.174 --> 00:01:25.773  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I didn't realize you were keeping track.

33
00:01:25.853 --> 00:01:27.892  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Oh, nervous and irascible.

34
00:01:27.973 --> 00:01:30.372  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
If you hadn't seen your wife
and child for two months,

35
00:01:30.452 --> 00:01:31.491  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
you'd be irascible, too.

36
00:01:31.572 --> 00:01:32.731  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Oh, believe me, I'm looking forward

37
00:01:32.812 --> 00:01:34.371  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
to Keiko and Molly's visit
as much as you are.

38
00:01:34.451 --> 00:01:35.651  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I doubt that.

39
00:01:35.730 --> 00:01:39.209  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
How many games of racquetball
have we played in the last two months?

40
00:01:39.289 --> 00:01:41.529  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I don't know. 15, maybe 20.

41
00:01:41.608 --> 00:01:42.968  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
No, try 70.

42
00:01:43.487 --> 00:01:44.528  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I've been keeping track of that, too.

43
00:01:44.608 --> 00:01:46.407  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
You know what all those games
have proved to me?

44
00:01:46.487 --> 00:01:48.766  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
That I'm a poor substitute for your wife.

45
00:01:49.407 --> 00:01:51.605  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I could have told you that 60 games ago.

46
00:01:52.885 --> 00:01:55.484  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Thing is, they're only going
to be here for two days.

47
00:01:55.565 --> 00:01:57.204  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
That's barely enough time to say hello.

48
00:01:57.284 --> 00:02:00.838  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
And they're back to Bajor again
for another four months.

49
00:02:00.403 --> 00:02:02.243  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Four months?

50
00:02:02.322 --> 00:02:04.482  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Why, that's another
150 games of racquetball.

51
00:02:04.562 --> 00:02:07.818  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
I don't think my elbow
can take that kind of abuse.

52
00:02:07.161 --> 00:02:09.200  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Maybe you can try
and convince her to stay.

53
00:02:09.360 --> 00:02:10.680  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
No, no, I can't do that.

54
00:02:10.760 --> 00:02:12.395  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I mean, I'm the one who suggested she go

55
00:02:12.120 --> 00:02:14.399  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
on this agrobiology expedition
in the first place.

56
00:02:15.358 --> 00:02:18.158  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
No, we'll just have to make
the best of the little time we have.

57
00:02:18.797 --> 00:02:21.956  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Which means we can't waste
a second of the next two days.

58
00:02:33.333 --> 00:02:35.433  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Ah, <i>peldor joi, </i>Odo.

59
00:02:35.512 --> 00:02:38.152  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
<i>Peldor joi </i>to you, too, Major.

60
00:02:39.111 --> 00:02:40.431  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Well...

61
00:02:40.511 --> 00:02:42.110  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
It's, uh...

62
00:02:42.550 --> 00:02:46.269  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
It's hard to believe
the Promenade is this empty at midday.

63
00:02:46.349 --> 00:02:48.629  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Oh, calm before the storm.

64
00:02:48.708 --> 00:02:53.387  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
In a few hours, this place will be packed
with Bajorans celebrating the festival.

65
00:02:54.507 --> 00:02:59.225  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Actually, I was thinking
of joining you this year.

66
00:02:59.306 --> 00:03:00.185  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Really?

67
00:03:00.265 --> 00:03:01.745  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I don't see why not.

68
00:03:01.824 --> 00:03:04.983  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
None of my Bajoran deputies
work during the Gratitude Festival.

69
00:03:05.643 --> 00:03:06.703  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Why should I?

70
00:03:06.783 --> 00:03:10.662  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Besides, if I'm going to
live here with you humanoids

71
00:03:10.742 --> 00:03:14.420  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
I may as well immerse myself
in your rituals.

72
00:03:14.501 --> 00:03:16.740  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Well, then, we'll see each other later.

73
00:03:16.820 --> 00:03:18.380  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I'd like that.

74
00:03:18.659 --> 00:03:22.219  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
If you're not too busy
being the Presider at the festival.

75
00:03:22.538 --> 00:03:25.582  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
For you, I will make the time, Odo.

76
00:03:25.498 --> 00:03:27.856  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Just look for me. I'll be with Bareil.

77
00:03:28.657 --> 00:03:29.776  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Oh...

78
00:03:30.456 --> 00:03:34.615  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
I thought he'd be celebrating
the festival on Bajor.

79
00:03:34.695 --> 00:03:36.414  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
So did I. I'm glad I was wrong.

80
00:03:36.494 --> 00:03:37.774  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
He's arriving on the next shuttle.

81
00:03:38.374 --> 00:03:41.613  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Well... you'd better go.
It'll be here soon.

82
00:03:42.128 --> 00:03:43.452  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
You're right.

83
00:03:44.171 --> 00:03:46.811  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
-I'll see you at the festival.
-Ah.

84
00:04:00.872 --> 00:04:01.247  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Chief.

85
00:04:01.326 --> 00:04:03.665  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Major.

86
00:04:03.406 --> 00:04:05.885  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
-Keiko.
-Ah... Bareil.

87
00:04:06.405 --> 00:04:09.204  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
-Good luck.
-You, too.

88
00:04:15.353 --> 00:04:16.522  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Nerys...`

89
00:04:16.722 --> 00:04:18.522  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I am so glad to see you.

90
00:04:18.601 --> 00:04:19.841  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I missed you.

91
00:04:19.921 --> 00:04:21.561  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I missed you, too.

92
00:04:27.999 --> 00:04:29.198  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Miles.

93
00:04:29.278 --> 00:04:30.758  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Miles!

94
00:04:30.838 --> 00:04:32.779  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Oh, Keiko.

95
00:04:33.357 --> 00:04:35.769  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I'm so glad to see you.

96
00:04:35.157 --> 00:04:37.276  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I have had the worst trip.

97
00:04:37.356 --> 00:04:40.356  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Oh, really? I'm sorry to hear that.

98
00:04:40.115 --> 00:04:42.115  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Now that you're here
everything's going to be great.

99
00:04:43.154 --> 00:04:44.633  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Hello, sweetie.

100
00:04:44.714 --> 00:04:46.674  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
You ready to have
a great time with your dad?

101
00:04:46.753 --> 00:04:47.753  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
No.

102
00:04:48.433 --> 00:04:49.273  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Why not?

103
00:04:49.512 --> 00:04:51.672  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I don't feel so good.

104
00:04:51.752 --> 00:04:52.832  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Really?

105
00:04:52.911 --> 00:04:55.350  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Aw... tell Daddy what's wrong.

106
00:04:55.870 --> 00:04:57.310  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
-( retching )
-Ah!

107
00:04:57.390 --> 00:04:58.949  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
( gasps ) Oh...

108
00:04:59.309 --> 00:05:01.388  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
LWAXANA: Oh... you poor dear.

109
00:05:02.588 --> 00:05:04.708  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
I should never have given you
all that candy.

110
00:06:59.873 --> 00:07:02.472  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
I usually make it a point
to drop by Quark's

111
00:07:02.552 --> 00:07:05.317  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
three or four times a day
at random intervals.

112
00:07:05.112 --> 00:07:07.871  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:10.00% 
Just to let him know
I'm thinking about him

113
00:07:07.951 --> 00:07:12.670  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:10.00% 
but seeing today is a holiday
he'll be busier than usual.

114
00:07:12.749 --> 00:07:16.188  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:10.00% 
I suggest you station
a man there full time.

115
00:07:16.268 --> 00:07:17.388  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:10.00% 
I think that about covers it.

116
00:07:17.468 --> 00:07:19.147  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:10.00% 
If you need me, I'll be on the Promenade.

117
00:07:19.228 --> 00:07:21.746  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:10.00% 
LWAXANA: But don't call
unless it's an emergency.

118
00:07:22.786 --> 00:07:24.706  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:10.00% 
The Constable will be occupied.

119
00:07:25.426 --> 00:07:27.465  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:10.00% 
ODO: Madam Ambassador.

120
00:07:28.145 --> 00:07:31.664  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:10.00% 
Oh, do we have to be so formal?

121
00:07:36.543 --> 00:07:39.581  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:10.00% 
Didn't they teach you any manners
in Starfleet Academy?

122
00:07:39.661 --> 00:07:42.214  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:10.00% 
Be a dear, run along.

123
00:07:42.101 --> 00:07:44.860  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:10.00% 
The Constable and I have
a lot of catching up to do.

124
00:07:44.939 --> 00:07:46.659  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:10.00% 
Uh, come back in five minutes.

125
00:07:46.739 --> 00:07:48.579  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:10.00% 
Make that half an hour.

126
00:07:51.657 --> 00:07:53.138  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:10.00% 
So...

127
00:07:54.979 --> 00:07:55.977  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:10.00% 
what brings you to the station?

128
00:07:56.296 --> 00:07:57.616  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Well, officially I'm here

129
00:07:57.696 --> 00:08:00.815  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
as the Betazoid representative
to the Gratitude Festival

130
00:08:00.895 --> 00:08:06.733  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
but the truth is, I came to see you,
you poor, sweet, tortured man.

131
00:08:07.573 --> 00:08:08.733  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Excuse me?

132
00:08:08.812 --> 00:08:11.852  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Oh, well, I know the torment
you must be going through.

133
00:08:11.931 --> 00:08:14.451  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Well, to spend your whole life searching
for your people,

134
00:08:14.530 --> 00:08:18.610  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
only to discover that they're the leaders
of that awful Dominion.

135
00:08:19.489 --> 00:08:20.689  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
You heard about that.

136
00:08:20.769 --> 00:08:21.968  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Odo...

137
00:08:22.368 --> 00:08:23.688  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
don't worry.

138
00:08:24.407 --> 00:08:25.847  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I'm here to help you.

139
00:08:26.367 --> 00:08:28.806  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
What kind of help do you mean?

140
00:08:29.206 --> 00:08:32.125  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Oh, a sympathetic ear...

141
00:08:32.206 --> 00:08:34.365  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
a shoulder to cry on...

142
00:08:34.445 --> 00:08:36.204  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
a lap to melt in.

143
00:08:36.884 --> 00:08:37.884  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Ah.

144
00:08:38.244 --> 00:08:41.923  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Well, that's very considerate of you,
but unnecessary.

145
00:08:42.362 --> 00:08:44.202  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
My people are who they are.

146
00:08:44.281 --> 00:08:45.281  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I am who I am.

147
00:08:45.362 --> 00:08:46.801  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I've learned to accept that.

148
00:08:47.361 --> 00:08:49.840  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Oh, you brave soul.

149
00:08:50.680 --> 00:08:56.118  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Oh, why don't we go someplace quiet
and you can tell me all about it?

150
00:08:56.678 --> 00:08:59.397  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Actually, I was planning
to attend the opening

151
00:08:59.478 --> 00:09:01.357  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
of the Gratitude Festival this afternoon.

152
00:09:01.957 --> 00:09:02.956  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Oh...

153
00:09:03.370 --> 00:09:04.796  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Well, even better.

154
00:09:04.875 --> 00:09:07.915  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
First, a little fun and relaxation

155
00:09:07.995 --> 00:09:12.754  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
and then we can delve
into the depths of your pain.

156
00:09:12.833 --> 00:09:16.112  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
I'll freshen up and meet you
in front of the Bajoran Temple

157
00:09:16.193 --> 00:09:18.552  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
for the Presider's opening address.

158
00:09:20.911 --> 00:09:25.190  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
I promise you, Odo,
you'll never be alone again.

159
00:09:33.827 --> 00:09:35.671  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
( beep )

160
00:09:39.346 --> 00:09:40.865  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Level 23, Section 8.

161
00:09:41.345 --> 00:09:42.424  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Oh!

162
00:09:46.943 --> 00:09:49.630  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
We need to see each other more often.

163
00:09:49.142 --> 00:09:52.382  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Hmm, I wish we both weren't so busy.

164
00:09:57.180 --> 00:10:01.338  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
I never expected Kai Winn to make me
one of her principal advisors.

165
00:10:01.419 --> 00:10:03.138  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I think she asks your advice

166
00:10:03.219 --> 00:10:06.777  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
just so that she can do the exact opposite
of what you recommend.

167
00:10:06.857 --> 00:10:11.136  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
I know you don't like Winn
but the office has changed her.

168
00:10:11.856 --> 00:10:13.495  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
The Prophets chose well.

169
00:10:14.735 --> 00:10:20.173  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
So, why don't we leave
spiritual matters in their capable hands

170
00:10:20.253 --> 00:10:24.920  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
and uh, concentrate on enjoying ourselves?

171
00:10:24.172 --> 00:10:25.491  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I have to go.

172
00:10:25.931 --> 00:10:29.691  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
The festival doesn't start
for an hour.

173
00:10:29.770 --> 00:10:32.850  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
But I have to set up the Renewal Scrolls
along the Promenade

174
00:10:32.929 --> 00:10:33.889  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
but it won't take long.

175
00:10:33.969 --> 00:10:35.496  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Jadzia's promised to help me.

176
00:10:35.129 --> 00:10:36.808  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Hmm. Jadzia, of course.

177
00:10:37.328 --> 00:10:38.367  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I've never understood

178
00:10:38.448 --> 00:10:40.687  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
how the two of you
could be such good friends.

179
00:10:40.767 --> 00:10:42.526  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
She's so...

180
00:10:43.526 --> 00:10:44.766  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Unpredictable.

181
00:10:45.465 --> 00:10:46.126  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
And you're so...

182
00:10:46.445 --> 00:10:47.445  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Predictable?

183
00:10:47.525 --> 00:10:49.165  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I didn't mean it like that.

184
00:10:49.244 --> 00:10:52.724  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
It's just that she gets to spend
so much more time with you than I do.

185
00:10:53.723 --> 00:10:57.322  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Jadzia and I have been doing this
for the past two years.

186
00:10:57.402 --> 00:10:59.241  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
It's becoming a tradition.

187
00:10:59.321 --> 00:11:02.920  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
I was hoping we could start
a few traditions of our own.

188
00:11:03.113 --> 00:11:05.679  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
We will... later tonight.

189
00:11:17.316 --> 00:11:18.476  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
( sighs )

190
00:11:22.315 --> 00:11:24.634  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
( exhausted sigh )

191
00:11:26.342 --> 00:11:27.193  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Is she asleep?

192
00:11:27.593 --> 00:11:30.552  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
It looks like the medicine
Doctor Bashir prescribed is working.

193
00:11:30.991 --> 00:11:32.551  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Ooh, that's a relief.

194
00:11:34.191 --> 00:11:35.351  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
( sighs )

195
00:11:35.990 --> 00:11:37.310  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Rough trip?

196
00:11:37.390 --> 00:11:39.549  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Oh, it was a disaster.

197
00:11:40.189 --> 00:11:42.428  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I thought it would never end.

198
00:11:43.684 --> 00:11:44.427  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Well...

199
00:11:46.627 --> 00:11:47.987  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I'm glad you're home.

200
00:11:48.673 --> 00:11:49.546  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Me, too.

201
00:11:50.466 --> 00:11:52.145  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
We should get ready for the festival.

202
00:11:52.226 --> 00:11:53.545  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
The baby-sitter will be here any minute.

203
00:11:53.625 --> 00:11:55.544  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Oh, the festival.

204
00:11:56.544 --> 00:11:58.344  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
On the other hand...

205
00:11:59.703 --> 00:12:03.632  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
We could spend the rest of the day
locked away in our quarters.

206
00:12:04.782 --> 00:12:07.501  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Miles, what I really want to do is sleep.

207
00:12:08.261 --> 00:12:10.740  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Well... then maybe you should.

208
00:12:10.820 --> 00:12:12.539  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Miles, I didn't say I was going to.

209
00:12:12.620 --> 00:12:14.259  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I just meant I could use some.

210
00:12:14.339 --> 00:12:15.738  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
That's OK.

211
00:12:16.378 --> 00:12:18.983  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
If you need to sleep, go ahead.

212
00:12:18.177 --> 00:12:20.973  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
-I'll understand.
-No, you won't.

213
00:12:20.177 --> 00:12:21.257  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
You'll be disappointed

214
00:12:21.337 --> 00:12:24.456  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
and you'll start brooding
and stomping around like an Andorian bull.

215
00:12:24.536 --> 00:12:27.415  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Look, go or stay, sleep or don't.

216
00:12:27.495 --> 00:12:28.695  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
It's all the same to me.

217
00:12:28.775 --> 00:12:31.147  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Just tell me what you want to do,
and we'll do it.

218
00:12:31.942 --> 00:12:33.653  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Miles, I've been making decisions
all day long.

219
00:12:33.733 --> 00:12:34.733  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
You decide.

220
00:12:36.493 --> 00:12:37.492  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
OK.

221
00:12:38.572 --> 00:12:40.171  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
We'll go to the festival

222
00:12:40.492 --> 00:12:41.971  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
but we don't have to go right away.

223
00:12:42.509 --> 00:12:45.290  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
I mean, you can take time to relax
and then change into something nice.

224
00:12:45.769 --> 00:12:46.930  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Nice?

225
00:12:47.649 --> 00:12:48.689  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Yeah.

226
00:12:49.208 --> 00:12:50.568  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Like your red dress.

227
00:12:51.448 --> 00:12:53.567  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
My red dress? Really?

228
00:12:54.367 --> 00:12:56.367  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Is there something wrong
with your red dress?

229
00:12:56.846 --> 00:13:00.405  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
No. It's, it's...
Just a little tight, that's all.

230
00:13:01.204 --> 00:13:03.444  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Oh. That's why I like it.

231
00:13:05.603 --> 00:13:08.437  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
All right. If it'll make you happy,
I'll wear the red dress.

232
00:13:08.403 --> 00:13:11.602  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Look, forget the red dress, OK?
Just wear whatever you want.

233
00:13:11.682 --> 00:13:12.921  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Look...

234
00:13:13.141 --> 00:13:16.480  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Let's just try to enjoy the next two days.

235
00:13:17.400 --> 00:13:20.919  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
I'll change into something nice
and we'll go to the festival, OK?

236
00:13:21.638 --> 00:13:22.918  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Fine.

237
00:13:22.999 --> 00:13:24.958  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
( door opens, closes )

238
00:13:25.385 --> 00:13:27.677  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
( sighs ) I can hardly wait.

239
00:13:33.435 --> 00:13:35.395  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
( indistinct conversations )

240
00:13:39.753 --> 00:13:43.324  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
( ringing continues )

241
00:14:00.708 --> 00:14:06.466  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
( speaking native language )

242
00:14:17.302 --> 00:14:18.502  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
( applause )

243
00:14:22.221 --> 00:14:25.979  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
And now I have the honor

244
00:14:26.740 --> 00:14:30.498  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
of placing the first
Renewal Scroll into the fire.

245
00:14:33.617 --> 00:14:35.617  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
As the scrolls burn

246
00:14:35.696 --> 00:14:39.255  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
may our troubles turn to ashes with them.

247
00:14:44.614 --> 00:14:47.934  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
( cheering )

248
00:14:50.613 --> 00:14:52.851  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
And now, for the next 26 hours

249
00:14:52.932 --> 00:14:56.290  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I expect you all to enjoy yourselves.

250
00:14:56.371 --> 00:14:58.210  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I know I will.

251
00:15:00.249 --> 00:15:02.369  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
May the Prophets walk with us.

252
00:15:09.606 --> 00:15:11.926  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
( woodwinds playing )

253
00:15:19.763 --> 00:15:21.365  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
( groaning )

254
00:15:21.643 --> 00:15:23.831  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Jake, are you all right?

255
00:15:23.162 --> 00:15:25.481  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Uh, just felt funny there for a second.

256
00:15:25.802 --> 00:15:27.641  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
You're sure you're all right?

257
00:15:28.561 --> 00:15:29.801  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Yeah, Dad.

258
00:15:31.759 --> 00:15:33.479  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Never felt better.

259
00:15:45.396 --> 00:15:47.955  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Bareil? What are you looking for?

260
00:15:48.357 --> 00:15:50.394  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Hmm? Oh, nothing.

261
00:15:50.474 --> 00:15:52.794  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Just... just looking.

262
00:15:52.873 --> 00:15:53.993  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Hmm.

263
00:15:54.553 --> 00:15:55.673  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
<i>Peldor joi.</i>

264
00:15:55.752 --> 00:15:58.312  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Oh, Jake, how thoughtful. Thank you.

265
00:15:58.392 --> 00:16:01.191  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Uh, I know you're busy
but can I talk to you for a second?

266
00:16:01.271 --> 00:16:02.350  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Sure.

267
00:16:02.711 --> 00:16:04.830  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
In private. It's kind of personal.

268
00:16:04.910 --> 00:16:06.349  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Oh, um...

269
00:16:06.430 --> 00:16:08.698  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I'll be right back.

270
00:16:09.688 --> 00:16:12.108  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Now, Jake, what can I do for you?

271
00:16:12.347 --> 00:16:13.627  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Uh...

272
00:16:14.867 --> 00:16:16.107  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I need some advice.

273
00:16:16.186 --> 00:16:19.426  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
You see, there's this older woman
and I think we're perfect for each other.

274
00:16:19.625 --> 00:16:21.825  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Ah... and she doesn't.

275
00:16:21.905 --> 00:16:23.705  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I don't know what she thinks.

276
00:16:23.784 --> 00:16:27.503  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Well, Jake, my advice to you
is to tell Mardah how you feel.

277
00:16:27.583 --> 00:16:29.902  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
-That way you'll know--
-Mardah and I broke up.

278
00:16:30.742 --> 00:16:32.462  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
You broke up?

279
00:16:32.542 --> 00:16:33.621  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Well, then, who?

280
00:16:34.301 --> 00:16:35.341  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
You.

281
00:16:36.740 --> 00:16:37.820  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Me?

282
00:16:39.605 --> 00:16:40.420  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I love you, Nerys.

283
00:16:42.378 --> 00:16:43.859  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Want to go out with me?

284
00:16:49.696 --> 00:16:50.816  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Morn, it's hard to believe

285
00:16:50.896 --> 00:16:54.335  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
a handsome, fun-loving guy like you
could have so many problems.

286
00:16:54.415 --> 00:16:56.151  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
My advice to you is to burn this

287
00:16:56.947 --> 00:16:58.894  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
as quickly as possible
and don't look back.

288
00:17:05.531 --> 00:17:06.971  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Sage advice.

289
00:17:07.513 --> 00:17:09.513  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Vedek Bareil. It's good to see you.

290
00:17:09.130 --> 00:17:12.809  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Oh, you have such a wise, generous spirit.

291
00:17:13.889 --> 00:17:15.929  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I only wish I had a friend like you.

292
00:17:16.288 --> 00:17:18.482  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I think of you as a friend.

293
00:17:18.128 --> 00:17:19.368  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
You mean that?

294
00:17:19.888 --> 00:17:21.875  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Of course.

295
00:17:21.367 --> 00:17:25.462  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Oh, I'm glad because I was hoping

296
00:17:25.126 --> 00:17:28.165  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
that you and I could get
to know each other a little better.

297
00:17:33.963 --> 00:17:35.483  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
A lot better.

298
00:17:38.522 --> 00:17:39.922  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Excuse me.

299
00:17:41.481 --> 00:17:43.840  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
( music playing )

300
00:18:03.915 --> 00:18:06.114  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I love Bajoran music.

301
00:18:06.194 --> 00:18:09.731  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
It's so intelligent, so vital...

302
00:18:09.633 --> 00:18:11.992  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
It reminds me of you.

303
00:18:12.721 --> 00:18:14.671  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Oh, dance with me, Odo.

304
00:18:14.751 --> 00:18:17.308  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I'm sorry. I don't dance.

305
00:18:17.110 --> 00:18:18.390  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Nonsense.

306
00:18:18.670 --> 00:18:20.629  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I saw you moving to the music.

307
00:18:20.709 --> 00:18:22.549  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
That wasn't dancing.

308
00:18:22.628 --> 00:18:24.148  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
That was... swaying.

309
00:18:24.228 --> 00:18:25.228  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Oh...

310
00:18:25.308 --> 00:18:27.187  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
then sway with me, Odo.

311
00:18:27.667 --> 00:18:29.387  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Sway with me.

312
00:18:29.986 --> 00:18:33.745  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I just remembered. I'm needed in Security.

313
00:18:34.545 --> 00:18:35.744  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
( sighs )

314
00:18:36.184 --> 00:18:37.624  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I'll come with you.

315
00:18:38.464 --> 00:18:40.743  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Ah, hello, Lieutenant.

316
00:18:40.823 --> 00:18:43.142  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
-Having a good time?
-No.

317
00:18:43.223 --> 00:18:44.742  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
( grunts in agreement )

318
00:18:50.740 --> 00:18:52.598  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
That's right.

319
00:18:52.140 --> 00:18:56.194  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Genuine latinum-plated
Renewal Scroll inscription pens

320
00:18:56.990 --> 00:19:00.980  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
blessed by Vedek Redab himself
shortly before he passed away.

321
00:19:00.177 --> 00:19:01.897  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Each pen is engraved with the words

322
00:19:01.977 --> 00:19:05.256  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
"Deep Space 9's Third Annual
Gratitude Festival,"

323
00:19:05.336 --> 00:19:09.614  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
today's date, and a lovely portrait
of the station by Ermat Zimm.

324
00:19:09.695 --> 00:19:11.734  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
So, get them while you can!

325
00:19:11.814 --> 00:19:14.413  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
They're sure to become collectors' items.

326
00:19:14.493 --> 00:19:16.573  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
( indistinct conversations )

327
00:19:22.930 --> 00:19:24.250  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Oh!

328
00:19:31.528 --> 00:19:32.488  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
So...

329
00:19:33.607 --> 00:19:36.526  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
What do you say we take a walk
around the Promenade for a while?

330
00:19:36.607 --> 00:19:38.446  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I'd rather stay here.

331
00:19:38.526 --> 00:19:42.365  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
I-I never thought I'd say this
but I kind of miss Quark's.

332
00:19:43.445 --> 00:19:45.683  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
The noise, the excitement...

333
00:19:45.764 --> 00:19:46.763  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
our table.

334
00:19:49.309 --> 00:19:50.642  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
You know...

335
00:19:50.723 --> 00:19:52.642  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I haven't sat here since you've been gone.

336
00:19:53.481 --> 00:19:56.280  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Oh, that's so sweet.

337
00:19:57.800 --> 00:19:59.320  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
So, how's the survey been going?

338
00:20:00.119 --> 00:20:02.919  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Uh... the terrain's
rougher than we expected

339
00:20:02.998 --> 00:20:05.798  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
and the ecosystem's a lot more diverse

340
00:20:05.878 --> 00:20:07.837  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
than it looked from the orbital scans.

341
00:20:07.917 --> 00:20:10.157  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
All in all, it's been pretty grueling.

342
00:20:10.236 --> 00:20:11.476  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Really?

343
00:20:11.556 --> 00:20:14.675  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Don't get me wrong.
I'm having a wonderful time.

344
00:20:15.714 --> 00:20:16.714  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
That's good.

345
00:20:17.354 --> 00:20:20.433  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
There is one problem
I have to talk to you about.

346
00:20:20.513 --> 00:20:23.832  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
It looks like the project's
taking longer than we hoped.

347
00:20:24.792 --> 00:20:26.791  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
What do you mean, "longer"?

348
00:20:27.192 --> 00:20:29.150  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
You have to understand, Miles,

349
00:20:29.231 --> 00:20:32.950  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
every valley has
an entirely different ecosystem.

350
00:20:33.300 --> 00:20:34.589  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
There's a lot of work to be done.

351
00:20:35.692 --> 00:20:37.388  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
But how much longer is it going to take?

352
00:20:38.682 --> 00:20:39.587  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I'm... I'm not sure.

353
00:20:40.279 --> 00:20:41.387  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Try a guess.

354
00:20:41.467 --> 00:20:44.546  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Uh, you know, an extra couple of days?
A week? Two?

355
00:20:44.626 --> 00:20:47.105  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
More like two or three months.

356
00:20:47.505 --> 00:20:48.585  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
You're telling me

357
00:20:48.665 --> 00:20:51.424  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
you're going to be on Bajor
for another seven months?

358
00:20:52.303 --> 00:20:54.823  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
It's either that or ask them
to find another botanist.

359
00:20:54.903 --> 00:20:57.182  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Maybe that's something worth considering.

360
00:20:57.942 --> 00:21:00.541  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
-Are you asking me to resign?
-No...

361
00:21:00.621 --> 00:21:03.101  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
but seven more months?

362
00:21:03.180 --> 00:21:05.500  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I don't like this any more than you do.

363
00:21:05.580 --> 00:21:07.339  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
You just said you were
having a great time.

364
00:21:07.699 --> 00:21:08.859  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Oh, I'm sorry.

365
00:21:08.939 --> 00:21:11.938  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
I suppose you'd be happier
if I were miserable?

366
00:21:12.186 --> 00:21:13.457  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I didn't say that.

367
00:21:16.537 --> 00:21:20.156  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
( sighing ) Sebarr was right.
I never should've mentioned it.

368
00:21:20.815 --> 00:21:22.255  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Who's Sebarr?

369
00:21:22.334 --> 00:21:24.334  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
He's one of the zoologists
I'm working with.

370
00:21:24.414 --> 00:21:28.538  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
He warned me not to talk to you about this
until after the Gratitude Festival.

371
00:21:28.133 --> 00:21:30.931  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
And who's he to be giving you advice?

372
00:21:31.572 --> 00:21:32.931  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
He's a friend.

373
00:21:33.115 --> 00:21:34.291  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
A friend?

374
00:21:35.610 --> 00:21:36.890  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I thought you were down there working.

375
00:21:37.410 --> 00:21:38.730  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
We are working.

376
00:21:39.209 --> 00:21:42.409  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Yeah, with time out for intimate
little chats about our relationship?

377
00:21:43.487 --> 00:21:44.848  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
What else did you tell him about us?

378
00:21:46.128 --> 00:21:49.527  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Miles, you're behaving like a child.

379
00:21:49.606 --> 00:21:51.166  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
What do you want me to say?

380
00:21:51.246 --> 00:21:54.725  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
I want you to say
that you're not going back...

381
00:21:55.245 --> 00:21:57.324  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
that you're going to stay here with me.

382
00:21:58.523 --> 00:22:03.426  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Miles, right now I don't even want
to sit at the same table with you.

383
00:22:03.963 --> 00:22:05.442  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Fine.

384
00:22:05.842 --> 00:22:07.841  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Well, go on.
Leave.

385
00:22:08.641 --> 00:22:11.680  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Go back to Bajor and your plants
and Sebarr.

386
00:22:13.639 --> 00:22:14.879  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
See if I care!

387
00:22:40.111 --> 00:22:42.270  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Whoa!
Slow down.

388
00:22:43.471 --> 00:22:44.470  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Hi, Dad.

389
00:22:44.950 --> 00:22:46.470  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I've been looking all over for you.

390
00:22:46.549 --> 00:22:47.549  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
In case you've forgotten,

391
00:22:47.629 --> 00:22:49.589  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
we're hosting a Gratitude Dinner
tonight in the Wardroom.

392
00:22:49.668 --> 00:22:51.428  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I could use your help in getting ready.

393
00:22:51.508 --> 00:22:53.667  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
I'm kind of busy right now, Dad.
I-I have to find someone.

394
00:22:53.748 --> 00:22:54.987  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Oh, Major Kira?

395
00:22:55.347 --> 00:22:56.986  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
-How'd you know?
-I just spoke to her.

396
00:22:57.664 --> 00:22:59.265  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
-Really? Where is she?
-Ah, just hold on!

397
00:22:59.346 --> 00:23:00.825  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
But I have to talk to her.

398
00:23:00.905 --> 00:23:03.305  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
You know, you were right about me
meeting someone at the festival.

399
00:23:03.384 --> 00:23:05.544  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I did not mean Major Kira.

400
00:23:05.624 --> 00:23:07.983  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
-You like her, don't you?
-Well, of course I like her.

401
00:23:08.633 --> 00:23:09.103  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Well, so do I.

402
00:23:09.183 --> 00:23:13.581  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
( sighs ) Jake,
what you're feeling now is just a crush.

403
00:23:14.501 --> 00:23:16.300  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Look, Jake...

404
00:23:19.419 --> 00:23:21.179  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Right now,

405
00:23:21.259 --> 00:23:23.899  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
you are confused, vulnerable, hurt.

406
00:23:23.978 --> 00:23:24.938  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
You miss Mardah.

407
00:23:25.179 --> 00:23:26.297  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Mardah was a mistake.

408
00:23:26.378 --> 00:23:28.657  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
She was too young, too immature for me.

409
00:23:29.136 --> 00:23:30.337  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Major Kira is a woman.

410
00:23:30.416 --> 00:23:32.575  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Major Kira is in love with Vedek Bareil.

411
00:23:32.656 --> 00:23:34.775  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
It won't last. He's always on Bajor.

412
00:23:35.551 --> 00:23:37.974  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
She needs someone who can
be with her all the time, like me.

413
00:23:38.854 --> 00:23:41.813  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
( sighs ) Jake,
I don't want to see you hurt again.

414
00:23:42.213 --> 00:23:43.732  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I appreciate that.

415
00:23:45.127 --> 00:23:46.691  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
But this is between Nerys and me.

416
00:23:47.611 --> 00:23:50.450  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Don't worry.
Everything's going to be fine.

417
00:23:50.530 --> 00:23:51.850  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Thanks.

418
00:23:54.449 --> 00:23:56.649  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I really can't accept this.

419
00:23:56.728 --> 00:23:58.328  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
But I want you to have it.
It's my gift to you.

420
00:23:58.408 --> 00:24:01.807  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Well, that's very thoughtful of you
but I have nothing to give you in return.

421
00:24:01.887 --> 00:24:04.726  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Being with you is the only present I need.

422
00:24:05.605 --> 00:24:06.885  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Now, come on.

423
00:24:06.966 --> 00:24:09.448  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Let's go write our Renewal Scrolls.

424
00:24:23.281 --> 00:24:25.407  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
<i>Peldor joi, </i>Chief.

425
00:24:25.120 --> 00:24:26.919  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
You look terrible.

426
00:24:27.439 --> 00:24:29.239  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
It's just a little headache, that's all.

427
00:24:29.318 --> 00:24:32.386  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Here. Have a free pen.

428
00:24:33.717 --> 00:24:34.757  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
What for?

429
00:24:34.837 --> 00:24:37.476  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
To write down your problems
on a Renewal Scroll.

430
00:24:37.556 --> 00:24:39.716  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
There isn't a scroll long enough
for all my problems.

431
00:24:39.795 --> 00:24:43.514  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Really? I thought you could sum them up
with one word...

432
00:24:43.594 --> 00:24:44.954  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Keiko.

433
00:24:45.913 --> 00:24:47.313  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Tell me I'm wrong.

434
00:24:48.393 --> 00:24:50.553  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
If you ask me, it's your own fault.

435
00:24:50.632 --> 00:24:53.152  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
You never should have let her
go to Bajor in the first place.

436
00:24:53.231 --> 00:24:55.631  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
What was I supposed to do?
Force her to stay here with me?

437
00:24:55.711 --> 00:24:57.670  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
That would have been a good start.

438
00:24:57.750 --> 00:25:00.697  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
You hu-mans, you never learn.

439
00:25:00.150 --> 00:25:04.668  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
You let your women go out in public,
hold jobs,

440
00:25:04.748 --> 00:25:05.868  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
wear clothing,

441
00:25:05.947 --> 00:25:08.187  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
and you wonder why your
marriages fall apart.

442
00:25:08.267 --> 00:25:10.106  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
That's your solution, Quark, huh?

443
00:25:10.186 --> 00:25:12.666  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Treat women like property?

444
00:25:12.146 --> 00:25:13.665  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Criticize it all you want,

445
00:25:13.745 --> 00:25:17.944  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
but on the Ferengi homeworld
husbands and wives never argue.

446
00:25:18.264 --> 00:25:21.423  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
There's no divorce, no broken homes...

447
00:25:21.503 --> 00:25:25.541  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Nothing but peaceful conjugal bliss.

448
00:25:26.221 --> 00:25:30.181  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
If Ferengi marriages are so wonderful
why are you still single?

449
00:25:31.500 --> 00:25:33.539  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I haven't met the right woman yet.

450
00:25:34.419 --> 00:25:35.939  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Well, I have.

451
00:25:36.579 --> 00:25:38.977  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
She just walked out that door.

452
00:25:39.377 --> 00:25:41.297  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
And out of your life.

453
00:25:43.376 --> 00:25:45.176  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Not if I can help it.

454
00:25:57.892 --> 00:25:59.925  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Bareil!

455
00:25:59.172 --> 00:26:01.531  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I was wondering where you disappeared to.

456
00:26:02.850 --> 00:26:05.250  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Come on, you can do better than that.

457
00:26:05.330 --> 00:26:07.449  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Someone might see us.

458
00:26:07.529 --> 00:26:10.209  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
We are the only people here.

459
00:26:10.769 --> 00:26:13.247  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Everyone else is on the Promenade.

460
00:26:17.526 --> 00:26:21.326  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
We have two hours before we're supposed
to join Commander Sisko for dinner.

461
00:26:22.765 --> 00:26:25.843  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
That gives us some time
to be alone together.

462
00:26:25.764 --> 00:26:27.603  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I... I can't. Um...

463
00:26:28.363 --> 00:26:29.403  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Why not?

464
00:26:29.763 --> 00:26:31.242  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I have to find Jadzia.

465
00:26:31.842 --> 00:26:33.441  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Jadzia? Is there something wrong?

466
00:26:33.522 --> 00:26:34.921  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
No, not at all.

467
00:26:35.361 --> 00:26:36.521  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Do you know where she is?

468
00:26:37.481 --> 00:26:40.119  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
She's probably on the Promenade.

469
00:26:40.200 --> 00:26:42.439  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
She wasn't there the last time I looked.

470
00:26:42.519 --> 00:26:45.238  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Why is it so important
for you to see Jadzia?

471
00:26:45.678 --> 00:26:48.117  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I'll explain everything later.

472
00:26:49.117 --> 00:26:50.357  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Uh...

473
00:26:51.836 --> 00:26:52.956  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Thank you, Nerys.

474
00:26:53.315 --> 00:26:54.356  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
For what?

475
00:26:54.675 --> 00:26:56.515  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
For being such a good friend.

476
00:27:00.873 --> 00:27:02.313  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Friend?

477
00:27:05.392 --> 00:27:06.871  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Dax...

478
00:27:06.952 --> 00:27:08.151  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
what are you doing here?

479
00:27:08.231 --> 00:27:10.830  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
I thought you might need some help
getting ready for the party.

480
00:27:10.910 --> 00:27:13.709  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Thanks, but that won't be necessary.

481
00:27:13.789 --> 00:27:16.269  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Wouldn't you rather be celebrating
on the Promenade?

482
00:27:16.348 --> 00:27:19.467  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
No, thanks. I don't want to run
into Vedek Bareil.

483
00:27:19.548 --> 00:27:22.387  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Oh, is there a problem between you?

484
00:27:22.467 --> 00:27:24.586  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
He can't keep his hands off me.

485
00:27:25.426 --> 00:27:27.705  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
That doesn't sound like Vedek Bareil.

486
00:27:27.785 --> 00:27:29.255  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I couldn't believe it myself

487
00:27:29.105 --> 00:27:31.648  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
but he wouldn't leave me alone.

488
00:27:31.144 --> 00:27:33.984  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
He's probably still out there
looking for me.

489
00:27:34.623 --> 00:27:36.234  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Have you told Kira?

490
00:27:36.742 --> 00:27:38.103  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I don't know how.

491
00:27:38.182 --> 00:27:40.102  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
It's going to break her heart.

492
00:27:40.861 --> 00:27:42.981  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
( sighs ) Someone has to tell her.

493
00:27:45.700 --> 00:27:47.260  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Do you want me to do it?

494
00:27:47.339 --> 00:27:48.419  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Would you?

495
00:27:51.218 --> 00:27:52.498  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Well...

496
00:27:53.738 --> 00:27:55.977  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
if you think that's the
best way to handle it.

497
00:27:56.576 --> 00:27:57.376  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
( sighs )

498
00:27:57.456 --> 00:27:59.256  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I'd really appreciate it, Benjamin.

499
00:27:59.336 --> 00:28:01.495  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I mean, this whole thing is ridiculous.

500
00:28:02.153 --> 00:28:04.214  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
How could I be interested in Bareil?

501
00:28:05.774 --> 00:28:07.414  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
We both know...

502
00:28:07.493 --> 00:28:09.413  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
It's always been you.

503
00:28:14.411 --> 00:28:16.291  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
( stammering )

504
00:28:22.649 --> 00:28:23.729  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Dax...

505
00:28:24.128 --> 00:28:25.483  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Hmm?

506
00:28:25.128 --> 00:28:28.647  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
-What are you doing?
-Making myself comfortable.

507
00:28:31.126 --> 00:28:34.166  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Have I ever told you
that you smell wonderful?

508
00:28:40.884 --> 00:28:46.322  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Ah, you know, old man, I have to admit
you had me going there for a minute.

509
00:28:49.521 --> 00:28:52.960  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Benjamin, stop acting so coy.
There's no one around.

510
00:28:53.760 --> 00:28:55.159  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I have an idea.

511
00:28:55.239 --> 00:28:59.877  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
You cancel the party, and then, that way
we can spend the evening alone together.

512
00:28:59.958 --> 00:29:02.957  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
-What do you say?
-Oh... uh...

513
00:29:03.370 --> 00:29:05.596  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
-Sisko to Bashir.
-BASHIR: <i>Go ahead, Commander.</i>

514
00:29:06.116 --> 00:29:08.315  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Meet me in the Infirmary immediately.

515
00:29:08.395 --> 00:29:09.315  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
<i>Aye, sir.</i>

516
00:29:09.874 --> 00:29:11.754  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
BASHIR: Her vital signs are normal.

517
00:29:11.834 --> 00:29:13.673  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Her brain activity is normal.

518
00:29:13.754 --> 00:29:17.233  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
No sign of infection or intoxication
of any kind.

519
00:29:17.592 --> 00:29:19.232  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
She's the picture of health.

520
00:29:19.311 --> 00:29:20.472  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
DAX: Told you.

521
00:29:20.792 --> 00:29:22.511  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Then why did you put
your head on my chest?

522
00:29:22.590 --> 00:29:24.351  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Oh, Julian, you should have seen his face.

523
00:29:24.430 --> 00:29:26.989  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Admit it, you were
this far away from total panic.

524
00:29:27.701 --> 00:29:29.389  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
BASHIR: I think we've both been
victims of a practical joke.

525
00:29:29.468 --> 00:29:31.748  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
At least someone around here
has a sense of humor.

526
00:29:34.107 --> 00:29:36.268  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Um, see you at the party, Julian.

527
00:29:44.624 --> 00:29:47.183  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
I've never been so embarrassed
in all my life,

528
00:29:47.263 --> 00:29:48.783  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
making me go through all those tests.

529
00:29:48.863 --> 00:29:50.862  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
It's your fault, Dax.
You took this one too far.

530
00:29:50.943 --> 00:29:54.222  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Oh, if I didn't love you so much
I'd be angry with you.

531
00:29:54.301 --> 00:29:55.581  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
See you at the party.

532
00:30:08.577 --> 00:30:10.296  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
( sighs )

533
00:30:11.377 --> 00:30:13.576  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
You look like you could use
a little cheering up.

534
00:30:13.656 --> 00:30:15.895  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
-Jake, do me a favor.
-Anything.

535
00:30:15.975 --> 00:30:17.547  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Leave me alone.

536
00:30:17.135 --> 00:30:18.414  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Uh...

537
00:30:18.494 --> 00:30:19.814  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
( sighs )

538
00:30:26.931 --> 00:30:28.411  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
( door opens )

539
00:30:35.369 --> 00:30:37.208  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
-Hi, sweetie.
-Hi.

540
00:30:37.448 --> 00:30:39.328  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
-Feeling better?
-Lots better.

541
00:30:39.408 --> 00:30:41.408  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Ah, that's what I wanted to hear.

542
00:30:41.487 --> 00:30:42.806  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
( snorting )

543
00:30:43.967 --> 00:30:46.805  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
-Where's Mommy?
-In her room, sad.

544
00:30:47.325 --> 00:30:50.848  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Oh. Well, listen,
why don't you go and play with Piggy

545
00:30:50.165 --> 00:30:51.604  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
in your room for a while

546
00:30:51.684 --> 00:30:54.443  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
and we'll see if Daddy
can cheer Mommy up, huh?

547
00:31:07.519 --> 00:31:09.838  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Keiko, it's me.
Can I come in?

548
00:31:09.919 --> 00:31:11.638  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Not now, Miles.

549
00:31:14.517 --> 00:31:18.236  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
You're right.
I'm an idiot... sometimes.

550
00:31:18.316 --> 00:31:19.596  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
If I don't get my own way

551
00:31:19.675 --> 00:31:22.755  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
I can be selfish
and childish and pigheaded.

552
00:31:23.834 --> 00:31:26.874  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
I said some things to you
that were pretty stupid.

553
00:31:27.474 --> 00:31:29.313  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I wish I could take them back.

554
00:31:36.670 --> 00:31:38.870  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
But even if it's too late for that, I...

555
00:31:39.630 --> 00:31:42.309  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
There's one thing
I want you to know, Keiko...

556
00:31:42.389 --> 00:31:43.948  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I... I love you.

557
00:31:44.708 --> 00:31:47.107  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I always have and I always will.

558
00:31:50.270 --> 00:31:52.306  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
I want you to know
I've left a letter of resignation

559
00:31:52.386 --> 00:31:54.425  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
on Commander Sisko's desk.

560
00:31:54.505 --> 00:31:57.424  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
I'm ready to move down to Bajor
with you tomorrow

561
00:31:57.505 --> 00:31:58.864  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
if you'll have me.

562
00:31:58.944 --> 00:32:00.943  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
And after that,
if you want to move back to Earth

563
00:32:01.239 --> 00:32:02.582  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
that's OK, too.

564
00:32:02.663 --> 00:32:04.542  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I'll do whatever it takes.

565
00:32:06.662 --> 00:32:08.421  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I just don't want to lose you.

566
00:32:11.180 --> 00:32:14.601  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Honey, did you hear what I said?

567
00:32:14.780 --> 00:32:15.939  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Yes.

568
00:32:16.139 --> 00:32:17.379  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
And?

569
00:32:18.258 --> 00:32:20.137  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
And I need time to think.

570
00:32:21.177 --> 00:32:23.570  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Why don't you go
to Commander Sisko's party?

571
00:32:23.137 --> 00:32:25.176  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
We can talk when you get back.

572
00:32:28.560 --> 00:32:29.894  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
If that's what you want.

573
00:32:34.453 --> 00:32:35.733  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
-Major...
-Ah!

574
00:32:35.813 --> 00:32:37.972  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Aren't you headed in the wrong direction?

575
00:32:39.252 --> 00:32:41.531  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
-Commander Sisko's party?
-Oh, I'm not going.

576
00:32:41.611 --> 00:32:44.410  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
-Why ever not?
-Because Bareil will be there.

577
00:32:44.690 --> 00:32:47.960  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
I thought the two of you
were very happy together.

578
00:32:47.901 --> 00:32:50.891  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
So did I, but it turns out
he'd rather be with Dax than me.

579
00:32:50.168 --> 00:32:52.808  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
And to make matters worse,
I have Jake Sisko chasing me

580
00:32:52.888 --> 00:32:55.247  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
around the station
professing his undying love.

581
00:32:55.327 --> 00:32:56.326  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
BASHIR: Well, that's strange.

582
00:32:56.407 --> 00:32:59.326  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
A little while ago
Jadzia had Commander Sisko convinced

583
00:32:59.406 --> 00:33:00.406  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
that she was in love with him.

584
00:33:00.485 --> 00:33:02.765  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
He even had me examine her
to make sure she was all right.

585
00:33:02.845 --> 00:33:04.644  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Apparently, it was only a joke.

586
00:33:04.724 --> 00:33:06.244  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Well, are you sure?

587
00:33:06.324 --> 00:33:08.443  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
People are acting very strangely today.

588
00:33:09.341 --> 00:33:12.442  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Maybe I should take another look
at Jadzia's test results.

589
00:33:12.522 --> 00:33:13.481  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Excuse me.

590
00:33:13.562 --> 00:33:16.721  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Constable, would you tell Commander Sisko
that I'll be a little late?

591
00:33:22.798 --> 00:33:25.558  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Oh, I should be getting to the Infirmary.

592
00:33:25.638 --> 00:33:26.957  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I'll join you.

593
00:33:27.375 --> 00:33:30.956  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
( groans ) Maybe you should examine
Bareil and Jake while you're at it.

594
00:33:31.365 --> 00:33:32.756  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
That wouldn't be a bad idea.

595
00:33:35.475 --> 00:33:37.954  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Oh, this won't take long.

596
00:33:51.151 --> 00:33:52.710  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Oh, what is it, Odo?

597
00:33:52.790 --> 00:33:55.469  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
I may not be able to read your emotions
but I can read your expression.

598
00:33:55.549 --> 00:33:57.228  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
-Something's wrong.
-I'm fine.

599
00:33:57.309 --> 00:33:59.947  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
I wish you'd tell me what's bothering you.
Maybe it would help you.

600
00:34:00.282 --> 00:34:02.787  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
As soon as something bothers me
I'll let you know, I promise.

601
00:34:02.867 --> 00:34:04.546  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Why do I find stubborn men so attractive?

602
00:34:04.626 --> 00:34:06.265  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
( groans )

603
00:34:06.346 --> 00:34:07.905  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
( sighs )

604
00:34:07.985 --> 00:34:10.305  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Would you please stop following me?

605
00:34:10.384 --> 00:34:13.224  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Oh, gladly,
if you'll just stop running away.

606
00:34:13.304 --> 00:34:17.982  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
I-I-I have something very important
to talk to you about.

607
00:34:18.624 --> 00:34:20.941  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Discuss it with Major Kira.
I'm not interested.

608
00:34:22.901 --> 00:34:24.940  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
But, Dad,
you promised that Nerys would be here!

609
00:34:25.210 --> 00:34:27.200  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
She will, and stop calling her Nerys.

610
00:34:27.539 --> 00:34:28.579  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
( gasps )

611
00:34:28.659 --> 00:34:30.138  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
<i>Peldor joi.</i>

612
00:34:30.739 --> 00:34:32.698  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Oh, Commander, I didn't realize

613
00:34:32.778 --> 00:34:34.537  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
that you and Lieutenant Dax
were that close.

614
00:34:34.618 --> 00:34:35.537  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
We're not.

615
00:34:35.617 --> 00:34:37.376  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Sisko to Bashir.

616
00:34:38.416 --> 00:34:40.815  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Computer, locate Dr. Bashir.

617
00:34:41.775 --> 00:34:43.854  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
COMPUTER: <i>Dr. Bashir is in the Infirmary.</i>

618
00:34:44.495 --> 00:34:48.693  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
( sighs ) Constable, go get Dr. Bashir
and bring him here immediately.

619
00:34:48.773 --> 00:34:50.493  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I'll be right back.

620
00:34:50.572 --> 00:34:51.772  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I'll go with you.

621
00:34:51.852 --> 00:34:53.851  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Yes, of course you will.

622
00:34:56.771 --> 00:34:58.730  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I wonder what Commander Sisko wanted.

623
00:34:58.810 --> 00:35:00.250  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Oh, it can wait.

624
00:35:02.529 --> 00:35:04.448  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
This is very embarrassing.

625
00:35:04.528 --> 00:35:06.568  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Yes, we have to stop.

626
00:35:07.208 --> 00:35:08.488  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Definitely.

627
00:35:11.566 --> 00:35:12.766  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Doctor!

628
00:35:15.565 --> 00:35:18.644  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Commander Sisko needs to see you
in the Wardroom.

629
00:35:19.204 --> 00:35:20.603  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Oh, tell him...

630
00:35:20.684 --> 00:35:22.523  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Oh, tell him I'll be there shortly.

631
00:35:22.603 --> 00:35:23.643  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Now, Doctor!

632
00:35:23.963 --> 00:35:25.202  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
You'd better go.

633
00:35:25.282 --> 00:35:26.642  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
( moans amorously )

634
00:35:27.161 --> 00:35:28.441  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Right.

635
00:35:32.360 --> 00:35:33.840  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
<i>Peldor joi.</i>

636
00:35:37.838 --> 00:35:40.780  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Please, Commander, step aside.

637
00:35:40.717 --> 00:35:42.916  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I need to speak to Jadzia.

638
00:35:42.997 --> 00:35:44.916  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I don't think she wants to speak with you.

639
00:35:44.996 --> 00:35:46.355  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
DAX: You tell him, Benjamin.

640
00:35:46.796 --> 00:35:49.115  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I... I only want to give her this.

641
00:35:49.515 --> 00:35:51.515  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
A Bajoran betrothal bracelet?

642
00:35:51.594 --> 00:35:53.834  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
It's been in my family for generations.

643
00:35:53.913 --> 00:35:54.993  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Can I see that?

644
00:35:57.592 --> 00:35:58.432  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I...

645
00:35:58.512 --> 00:36:01.392  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Nerys! Am I glad to see you.

646
00:36:01.471 --> 00:36:03.708  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Doctor... I need your help!

647
00:36:03.350 --> 00:36:05.708  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
And I need yours, too.

648
00:36:05.150 --> 00:36:06.789  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
You've got to get me away from Kira.

649
00:36:06.870 --> 00:36:08.869  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
I can't... ( gasps )
keep my hands off of her.

650
00:36:08.949 --> 00:36:11.308  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
What's worse
I can't keep my hands off him.

651
00:36:12.228 --> 00:36:13.428  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
( door opens )

652
00:36:15.307 --> 00:36:16.547  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
( sighs )

653
00:36:18.666 --> 00:36:20.625  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I can't explain it either.

654
00:36:21.665 --> 00:36:23.745  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
( gasps )

655
00:36:28.264 --> 00:36:29.783  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
( sighs )

656
00:36:35.661 --> 00:36:37.220  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
( <i>sighs </i>)

657
00:36:37.301 --> 00:36:38.980  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
She doesn't love me.

658
00:36:39.539 --> 00:36:40.700  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Who?

659
00:36:41.219 --> 00:36:42.499  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Nerys.

660
00:36:45.178 --> 00:36:46.178  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
( <i>sighs </i>)

661
00:36:46.257 --> 00:36:47.858  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
You're better off.

662
00:36:48.337 --> 00:36:50.816  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
In the end, they only break your heart.

663
00:36:50.897 --> 00:36:52.456  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
( door opens )

664
00:36:53.975 --> 00:36:56.957  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Although, sometimes it's worth it.

665
00:37:05.732 --> 00:37:07.292  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
What do you think?

666
00:37:07.971 --> 00:37:09.531  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
You look beautiful.

667
00:37:10.930 --> 00:37:13.969  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Did you really mean it
about turning in your resignation?

668
00:37:14.502 --> 00:37:14.969  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Mm-hmm.

669
00:37:15.609 --> 00:37:19.728  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Well, you'd better get it back
before Commander Sisko sees it.

670
00:37:20.648 --> 00:37:22.927  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
It was very nice of you to offer.

671
00:37:31.205 --> 00:37:33.283  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I love you so much.

672
00:37:38.962 --> 00:37:40.522  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
( laughing ) Hey!

673
00:37:41.361 --> 00:37:42.601  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
( lasciviously ) Oh...

674
00:37:44.201 --> 00:37:46.400  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Ooh...

675
00:37:46.120 --> 00:37:48.999  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Commander, here's that
I'danian spice pudding you ordered.

676
00:37:49.793 --> 00:37:51.678  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
I want to give this to you
as a token of my affection.

677
00:37:51.918 --> 00:37:53.157  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Oh, no, you don't!

678
00:37:53.758 --> 00:37:55.797  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Bareil, listen to me...

679
00:37:55.877 --> 00:37:57.836  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I'll fight for her if I have to!

680
00:37:59.156 --> 00:38:00.435  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
( grunts )

681
00:38:04.515 --> 00:38:06.473  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Oh, I'm sorry, Benjamin.

682
00:38:06.554 --> 00:38:08.753  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
He was just starting to annoy me.

683
00:38:08.833 --> 00:38:09.793  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
QUARK: Commander...

684
00:38:10.712 --> 00:38:12.952  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
You throw one hell of a party.

685
00:38:13.632 --> 00:38:16.551  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Pudding, anyone?
I've got I'danian spice pudding.

686
00:38:16.631 --> 00:38:17.910  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
( Bareil groans )

687
00:38:18.790 --> 00:38:20.270  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Are you all right?

688
00:38:20.790 --> 00:38:22.229  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
( groans )

689
00:38:22.869 --> 00:38:24.708  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Pudding, anyone?

690
00:38:25.628 --> 00:38:26.988  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Doctor?

691
00:38:27.587 --> 00:38:29.547  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
-Pudding, anyone?
-No, no, thank you.

692
00:38:29.626 --> 00:38:30.667  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Ooh!

693
00:38:31.586 --> 00:38:32.586  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
( groans )

694
00:38:39.824 --> 00:38:41.583  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I'll take one.

695
00:38:42.223 --> 00:38:43.742  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Help yourself.

696
00:38:45.622 --> 00:38:47.422  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Why did she hit me?

697
00:38:47.941 --> 00:38:49.461  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
( gasps )

698
00:38:50.101 --> 00:38:51.740  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Oh, forget about him.

699
00:38:51.821 --> 00:38:54.980  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
What about me? I need you, Keiko.

700
00:38:55.659 --> 00:38:57.778  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
My ears tingle at the sight of you.

701
00:38:57.859 --> 00:38:59.218  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Marry me.

702
00:38:59.298 --> 00:39:00.937  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
She's taken, Quark!

703
00:39:01.174 --> 00:39:02.457  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
( squealing )

704
00:39:02.537 --> 00:39:04.567  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Easy, Chief.

705
00:39:04.137 --> 00:39:05.936  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
He doesn't know what he's doing.

706
00:39:09.295 --> 00:39:11.546  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
What are you looking at me for?

707
00:39:11.454 --> 00:39:14.893  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Zanthi fever?
Oh, that's ridiculous.

708
00:39:14.974 --> 00:39:16.453  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
That, that's impossible.

709
00:39:16.532 --> 00:39:18.172  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
That only affects older Betazoids.

710
00:39:18.252 --> 00:39:20.211  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Well, that may be,
but according to my tests

711
00:39:20.292 --> 00:39:22.113  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
you show all the symptoms.

712
00:39:22.918 --> 00:39:25.250  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Zanthi fever is a virus
which affects the empathic abilities of...

713
00:39:25.330 --> 00:39:27.730  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
um... mature Betazoids.

714
00:39:27.809 --> 00:39:30.329  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
It causes them to project
their emotions onto others.

715
00:39:30.808 --> 00:39:34.728  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Then Mrs. Troi's amorous feelings
for... someone on the station

716
00:39:34.807 --> 00:39:36.567  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
were being passed along
to the people around her?

717
00:39:36.647 --> 00:39:37.607  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Well, not everyone.

718
00:39:37.686 --> 00:39:40.125  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Only those within close proximity to her
when she had an attack,

719
00:39:40.206 --> 00:39:41.605  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
and even then
there would have had to have been

720
00:39:41.685 --> 00:39:43.885  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
some preexisting latent attraction.

721
00:39:44.725 --> 00:39:48.123  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
-You're saying Dax...
-Only on a subconscious level.

722
00:39:48.483 --> 00:39:50.643  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Best not think about it too much,
if you ask me.

723
00:39:51.283 --> 00:39:53.442  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I am terribly sorry, Commander.

724
00:39:53.522 --> 00:39:55.641  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I hope I haven't caused too much trouble.

725
00:39:55.721 --> 00:39:58.680  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
I'm sure no permanent harm
was done, right, Doctor?

726
00:39:58.760 --> 00:40:01.519  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Oh, a simple wide-spectrum antiviral agent
should cure Mrs. Troi.

727
00:40:01.600 --> 00:40:02.679  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
And as for everyone else

728
00:40:02.759 --> 00:40:04.118  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
well, they'll be back to normal
in a day or two.

729
00:40:04.199 --> 00:40:05.238  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Excuse me.

730
00:40:05.998 --> 00:40:08.517  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
I promised Nerys that I'd meet her
in her quarters this evening.

731
00:40:09.797 --> 00:40:13.316  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
I think you ought to postpone that visit
for a day or two.

732
00:40:14.115 --> 00:40:15.475  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
( sigh )

733
00:40:16.714 --> 00:40:18.994  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
SISKO: <i>Commander's Log, supplemental.</i>

734
00:40:19.744 --> 00:40:21.354  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
<i>I'm happy to report </i>
<i>that Dr. Bashir's diagnosis</i>

735
00:40:21.433 --> 00:40:22.953  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
<i>has been proven correct.</i>

736
00:40:23.330 --> 00:40:26.192  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
<i>My son and all the others affected</i>
<i>by Mrs. Troi's condition </i>

737
00:40:26.272 --> 00:40:28.271  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
<i>have made full recoveries.</i>

738
00:40:28.351 --> 00:40:29.471  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
( Troi laughing )

739
00:40:29.551 --> 00:40:33.149  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
This is one Gratitude Festival
they'll be talking about for a long time.

740
00:40:33.230 --> 00:40:34.989  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I know I'll never forget it.

741
00:40:36.290 --> 00:40:38.908  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
I hope everything
works out for you, Odo...

742
00:40:38.988 --> 00:40:40.468  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
with Major Kira.

743
00:40:40.548 --> 00:40:42.427  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I... don't know what you mean.

744
00:40:42.507 --> 00:40:45.786  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Oh, don't worry.
Your secret's safe with me.

745
00:40:45.866 --> 00:40:48.226  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
After all, I know what it's like

746
00:40:48.305 --> 00:40:52.624  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
to be attracted to someone who doesn't
necessarily feel the same way.

747
00:40:55.863 --> 00:40:57.663  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
( sighs )

748
00:40:57.742 --> 00:41:00.181  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
If you get tired of waiting for her...

749
00:41:10.338 --> 00:41:12.186  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
...you know where to find me.

750
00:41:14.982 --> 00:41:15.577  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I'll keep that in mind.

751
00:41:22.415 --> 00:41:25.774  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
So, you're sure Dr. Bashir said
your test results were negative?

752
00:41:25.854 --> 00:41:28.133  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
That's right.
My headache was just a headache.

753
00:41:28.213 --> 00:41:30.133  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I never was affected by Mrs. Troi.

754
00:41:30.212 --> 00:41:34.692  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Well, I guess that means you don't have
a latent attraction to me, after all.

755
00:41:34.771 --> 00:41:36.411  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Nothing latent about it

756
00:41:36.490 --> 00:41:38.170  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
or weren't you paying
attention last night?

757
00:41:38.251 --> 00:41:40.104  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I was paying attention.

758
00:41:40.649 --> 00:41:42.849  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
You still have the touch, O'Brien.

759
00:41:45.809 --> 00:41:47.647  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
So do you.

760
00:41:52.566 --> 00:41:54.485  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
You take good care of Mommy, honey, OK?

761
00:41:54.566 --> 00:41:56.205  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I will.

762
00:42:04.563 --> 00:42:05.962  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
We'll see you in a few months.

763
00:42:06.425 --> 00:42:07.361  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I'll be here.

764
00:42:15.519 --> 00:42:16.759  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Chief?

765
00:42:19.957 --> 00:42:21.357  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
( both laughing )

